cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about learning word embeddings from free text.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper presents an algorithm for learning word embeddings.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as word embeddings are widely used in natural language processing tasks, which fall under the umbrella of AI.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses the skip-gram architecture from word2vec, which is a neural network model.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as word embeddings are used in network analysis and community detection tasks, which fall under the umbrella of information networks.
